With a built in combination lock, the Samsonite cases are good to go no matter where you are. No keys required. Expansion on All Sizes Design includes expansion for added packing capacity when needed. Consumer preferred expansion on all sizes. 360 Spinner Wheels This lightweight line offers heavyweight protection riding on effortless 360 degree Spinner Wheels. Don't pull your case: let Centric roll comfortably beside you on your journey.

TSA Combination Lock How to Use the TSA Combination Lock Our TSA-approved combination locks are simple and easy to use, no key required! Use a ballpoint pen or other pointed object to press the small button located near the dials. With the button pressed in, set the dials to your desired code, and slide the button with the key hole towards to the dials to set. The code is now ready to use. The key hole is intended only for use by TSA agents, and no keys are included or required to use our TSA combination locks. The factory default code for new luggage is 0-0-0.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Perfect for international travel. Just the right size, survived multiple trips and rolls great.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars SHINY, STYLISH, kinda durable!
reviews.reviewText: I bought these when I as going to INDIA for a 20 day trip. I travel a-lot and my a-lot means - travelled 5 countries in last 1 year. Most unique trait I enjoyed most about these suitcases which stood out from all the the other travelling bags - ok not all of them but most of them was that when these come out on conveyer belt on Airport you are not flipping each and every bag to see if that one is yours. Especially on International flights where there are like 400 people looking for their bag. You are the only one out of 400 bag that has this kind of Material and design. it has been 2 years now and I haven't seen similar bag on the airport yet. They have some scratches here and there. But they have survived and I also take good care of them. But they feel like they are made of cheap plastic. Seriously when I first received them. My first impression was what in world did I just order for 400$ this doest not even gives me a feel of 100$. But i guess samsonite has proved me them and it has survived quite a lot time. I do feel if you put a alright amount of pressure on them. They will break and shatter!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice little suitcase
reviews.reviewText: It’s hard to get excited about luggage but I do like this little bag. I especially like the built-in TSA lock, which keeps me from having to find my old locks every time I travel. This is a good size when traveling for a few days to a week (if you pack light), the wheels are smooth, the hard shell makes it easy to throw around, and the bag easily fits in the overhead compartments.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 25, 2018
reviews.reviewText: This is a good suitcase. Very durable I’ve been using it constantly over the past 5 months and with the way I’ve dropped it and how the airlines treat it it’s held up extremely well. It’s my first spinner suitcase and i don’t know how I went this long without one. It rolls very smoothly even though the wheels looks small and flimsy. I can push it wit( ease without having to raise the handle. But I’m only 5’5” so that works. It stores a lot and comes with an expander adding space to the bag. It also has the TSA lock though I haven’t used it.Two negatives: the handle as other reviewers have said is a bit flimsy as in when my bag weights 45+ pounds I always feel like using the handle to get it ,owing is going to snap the handle off or cause it to break. It’s the primary reason I just push it with the handle down. Other issue is the side handle is on the same side/half of the suitcase as the top handle. This screws with the center of gravity and makes the bag difficult to maneuver when it’s fully loaded or you’ve expanded it to full size. As I’ve seen most of samsonites luggage has the handles on the same side of the suitcase which is unfortunate.I would recommend. It was cheap, as someone who’s had multiple bags demolished by delta over the past 12 months (none were hardside) this was well worth the investment and it has kept my things dry when my bags have been moved out in the rain at airports with bad weather.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars For the price, excellent!
reviews.reviewText: This suitcase is big and is of good quality. It certainly is not a Rimowa or Tumi, but for our travel is sturdy enough and does the job. Rimowa has very light weight suitcases, which barely add anything to a scale. This one is not as light, but also not as heavy as no-name or low end brands. We had it for two years now roughly and it travelled a couple of times over the Atlantic - it is holding up great so far.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Looks much better in real life
reviews.reviewText: I wanted a Samsonite because they are expected to be more durable. I had an airline decline compensation when a wheel had come off on a "cheaper" suitcase. The inside is very roomy, it is very light, and looks actually much more stylish than in the pictures.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very Happy with this Set
reviews.reviewText: Bought these last year to replace older/heavier luggage. This set has been on several overseas trips and is holding up very well. Companions traveled with similar style sets, but they already look pretty beat up (creases, scuffs, scratches) compared to these. Heard horror stories about frail handles, but so far, so good.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Great luggage, APPALLING wheels.
reviews.reviewText: Real Jekyll and Hyde situation here.The good: everything you would expect from Samsonite. Lightweight, maneuverable, great packing features, easy on the eye.The bad: wheels that crumble like a cheap cookie. Seriously, what the actual F?? I knew something was wrong when it left tire tracks on my floor. After two easy domestic trips the wheel surfaces are disintegrating into a black powdery substance. Just rubbing your thumb over them takes off another layer. I'll be generous and say they probably got a dud batch of wheels for this production run, but clearly the quality control failed.Sure, I can return it to Samsonite for repair. But they make you pay shipping costs and there's always the risk they will weasel out of the warranty through some technicality.Avoid.
